# WHAT IT IS
#   Saleor Configurator is the canonical "config-as-code"
#   driver for Saleor — the open-source headless e-commerce
#   platform.  Point it at a Saleor instance's `/graphql/`
#   endpoint, hand it a bearer token, and it lets you:
#     • `introspect` the live store and dump it as a YAML
#       configuration manifest
#     • `diff` the local YAML against the live store to see
#       what would change
#     • `deploy` the local YAML to the live store (idempotent;
#       safe to re-run; `--plan` for dry-run)
#     • `validate` the YAML against the JSON schema without
#       hitting the network
#     • `schema` to emit the JSON Schema itself for editor
#       autocompletion + agent validation
#     • `recipe` to apply pre-built configuration templates
#     • `start` for the interactive first-time-setup wizard
#
#   Configurator manages products, channels, categories,
#   attributes, shipping zones, warehouses, tax classes, page
#   types, menus, permission groups, models, model types, and
#   every other declarative entity Saleor exposes through its
#   GraphQL API.  All operations are typed at compile-time via
#   `gql.tada`, the canonical type-level GraphQL client by
#   0no-co that derives complete TypeScript types from
#   `*.graphql` schema files directly inside the TypeScript
#   type system — no codegen step, no runtime overhead.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli/main.ts +
#                       src/commands/{deploy,diff,introspect,
#                       schema,start,validate,recipe}.ts
#                       Zod-schema + commander.js bindings,
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/saleor/
#                       configurator/contents/src/...`)
#
#   configurator [<SUBCOMMAND>] [args...]
#
#   Base flags  (apply to every command via
#                `baseCommandArgsSchema`):
#     --url <URL>                    Saleor instance URL
#                                    (`/graphql/`-suffixed)
#     --token <TOKEN>                Saleor API token
#                                    (Bearer)
#     --config <PATH>                Configuration file path
#                                    [default: config.yml]
#     --quiet                        Suppress output
#
#   Subcommands:
#     start                          Interactive first-time-
#                                    setup wizard
#
#     introspect [BASE-FLAGS]        Download the current
#                                    configuration from the
#                                    remote Saleor instance
#                                    into config.yml
#
#     diff [BASE-FLAGS]              Show differences between
#                                    local config.yml and the
#                                    remote Saleor instance
#
#     deploy [BASE-FLAGS] [OPTIONS]  Deploy local config.yml to
#                                    the remote Saleor instance
#       --report-path <PATH>           Write a structured
#                                      deployment report
#       --verbose                      Show detailed error
#                                      information
#       --json                         Output deployment results
#                                      in JSON format
#       --plan                         Show deployment plan
#                                      without executing
#       --fail-on-delete               Exit with error if any
#                                      deletions are detected
#       --skip-media                   Skip media fields during
#                                      deployment (preserves
#                                      target media)
#       --text                         Force human-readable
#                                      output even in non-TTY
#                                      mode
#
#     validate [--config <PATH>]     Validate the local config
#                                    file against the JSON
#                                    schema  (no network
#                                    required)
#
#     schema                         Output the JSON Schema for
#                                    config.yml  (for IDE
#                                    autocompletion + agent
#                                    validation)
#
#     recipe <SUB>                   Manage recipes
#                                    (pre-built configuration
#                                    templates)
#       list                           List available recipes
#       show <RECIPE>                  Preview a recipe's
#                                      configuration
#       apply <RECIPE> [BASE-FLAGS]    Apply a recipe to your
#                                      Saleor instance
#       export <RECIPE> <PATH>         Export a recipe to a
#                                      local file
#
#   Exit codes:
#     0   SUCCESS
#     1   GENERAL_ERROR
#     1   CI_DRIFT_DETECTED  (from `diff`)
#     2   INVALID_ARGS
#     3   FILE_NOT_FOUND
#     4   NETWORK_ERROR
#     5   PERMISSION_ERROR
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `gql.tada ^1.8.5` declared in
#   package.json — `gql.tada` is THE canonical type-level
#   GraphQL client for TypeScript, maintained by 0no-co (the
#   organization behind `urql`, the GraphQL client used at
#   Cloudflare, Stripe, GitLab, and many other production-
#   scale GraphQL deployments — 0no-co/gql.tada, 2,000+ stars;
#   the predominant type-first TypeScript GraphQL primitive
#   that derives complete `Result<>`/`Variables<>` types
#   directly from `*.graphql` schema files INSIDE the
#   TypeScript type system — no codegen step, no runtime
#   transform, no separate emit phase).  gql.tada exposes the
#   typed `graphql` template-literal tag from
#   `gql.tada/ts-plugin` or `gql.tada`:
#     `const TestQuery = graphql(`{ users { id name } }`)` ->
#     compile-time-typed `DocumentNode<{ users: { id: string;
#                                                    name:
#                                                    string }[]
#                                       }, {}>`,
#   the typed `initGraphQLTada<{ introspection,  scalars }>()`
#   factory that re-types every call site to your specific
#   schema's introspection, the typed
#   `readFragment(fragment, data)` masking utility, the
#   `FragmentOf<typeof T>` type-level helper for typed fragment
#   composition, `VariablesOf<typeof T>` for typed-variable
#   inference, `ResultOf<typeof T>` for typed-result inference,
#   `DocumentTypeDecoration` for typed network-layer integration
#   into urql / @apollo/client / graphql-request / @graphql-
#   hive/client wrappers, and the `gql.tada` CLI itself that
#   generates the per-schema introspection module
#   (`__generated__/graphql-env.d.ts`).  configurator's
#   `src/core/...` constructs typed GraphQL operations via
#   `graphql(...)` template-literal tags, dispatches them
#   against a `graphql-request`-style transport, and
#   round-trips between the Saleor schema and the local
#   `config.yml` via typed-Zod-validated entity models.
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/saleor/configurator/contents/package.json
#       → "gql.tada": "^1.8.5"
#       → "@commander-js/extra-typings"
#       → bin: { "@saleor/configurator": "./bin/cli.mjs",
